“The combined dataset contains 86,662 samples across more than 30 languages, with English comprising approximately 79% of the data. Among Indic languages, Tamil, Hindi, Malayalam, Gujarati, and Bengali are the most frequent. Based on language and script detection, 79% of samples are routed to XLM-RoBERTa, 4.8% to IndicBERT, and 15.9% to a translation-based fallback model. This distribution empirically validates the necessity of a hybrid, language-aware architecture.”